Copec Halts Production at South Chile Pulp Plant, Mercurio Says

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-03-08T10:27:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/copec-halts-production-at-south-chile-pulp-plant-mercurio-says.html
  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC) ,  Chile ’s biggest
pulp producer, closed its Valdivia plant because of low water
levels in the Cruces River,  El Mercurio  reported.  Copec’s third largest plant may resume operations in the
coming days because rain is forecast for the weekend, the
Santiago-based newspaper reported, citing people at the company
that it didn’t identify.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
